  "original_title": "\u2019\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Post may be revoked at any time'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Chief Whip of the Opposition, Laxman Kriyella, told the House that the President can remove Ranil Wickremesinghe from the post of Prime Minister at any time through the 22nd Amendment Act to be brought by the government.",
        "He said the above while responding to the Prime Minister's special announcement while attending the session of the Parliament yesterday.",
        "It is only through the 19th Amendment that the Departmental Supervisory Committees can function properly. However, in the absence of the 19th Amendment Act, no powers are conferred on this committee. He said that they have politicized all the groups by bringing the 21st Amendment Act. What Justice Minister Vijayadasa Rajapaksa is submitting is not the 19th Amendment Act. He also said that initially steps were taken to bring back the 19th Amendment Act, but later another amendment was being tried.",
        "Through this Act, the powers of the President have been increased instead of reduced. Thus, the President can remove Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe from the post of Prime Minister at any time. However, he also said that we do not want to remove Ranil from the post of Prime Minister.",
        "Lakshman Kiriella also said that he agrees with the prime minister's statement that committees should be set up under the Donamoor constitutional system. Ranil Wickramasinghe replied that there is no departmental oversight committee in the constitutions of any country. Therefore, we will discuss this together and come to a resolution, he said."
      ],
